{"paperId": "07ca445023b5b9af5989e71930cd4855a8a738fb", "title": "REFeREE: A REference-FREE Model-Based Metric for Text Simplification", "abstract": "Text simplification lacks a universal standard of quality, and annotated reference simplifications are scarce and costly. We propose to alleviate such limitations by introducing REFeREE, a reference-free model-based metric with a 3-stage curriculum. REFeREE leverages an arbitrarily scalable pretraining stage and can be applied to any quality standard as long as a small number of human annotations are available. Our experiments show that our metric outperforms existing reference-based metrics in predicting overall ratings and reaches competitive and consistent performance in predicting specific ratings while requiring no reference simplifications at inference time.", "venue": "International Conference on Language Resources and Evaluation", "year": 2024, "citationCount": 0, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "REFeREE is introduced, a reference-free model-based metric with a 3-stage curriculum that outperforms existing reference-based metrics in predicting overall ratings and reaches competitive and consistent performance in predicting specific ratings while requiring no reference simplifications at inference time."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [-0.16904520988464355, 0.6749938130378723, -0.3303599953651428, -0.28850194811820984, -0.5669524669647217, 0.047338735312223434, 0.4921407401561737, -0.18739494681358337, -0.2958782911300659, -0.1791834533214569, 0.33913832902908325, 0.3195205330848694, -0.2637558877468109, 0.17307890951633453, -0.012541407719254494, 0.5052475333213806, -0.43779823184013367, 0.5177663564682007, -0.30485931038856506, -0.7219254374504089, 0.20421907305717468, -0.6825118064880371, -0.7804369330406189, -0.20998728275299072, 0.941264808177948, 0.30559173226356506, -0.11096430569887161, 0.5452603101730347, -0.2449719756841659